<topic id='attribute_private_controlled_drug_prescriber_code.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Attribute: PRIVATE CONTROLLED DRUG PRESCRIBER CODE - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
A 
    <xref outputclass="attribute"
            keyref="attribute_private_controlled_drug_prescriber_code">PRIVATE CONTROLLED DRUG PRESCRIBER CODE</xref>
 is allocated by the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_nhs_prescription_services">NHS Prescription Services</xref>
 to private prescribers who prescribe schedule 2 and 3 controlled drugs that are intended to be dispensed by registered pharmacies.  </p>
  <p>
      <i>
Note: A registered pharmacy means 
      <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_pharmacy_premises">Pharmacy Premises</xref>
 registered with the 
      <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_general_pharmaceutical_council">General Pharmaceutical Council</xref>
 and listed on the 
      <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_general_pharmaceutical_council_register">General Pharmaceutical Council Register</xref>
      </i>
 .  </p>
  <p>
For information on Controlled Drugs, see the 
    <xref href="https://www.nhsbsa.nhs.uk/pharmacies-gp-practices-and-appliance-contractors/prescribing-and-dispensing/safer-management"
            scope="external"
            format="html">NHS Business Services Authority Prescription Pricing Division website.</xref>
  </p>
  <p>Private Controlled Drug Prescribers fall into one of the following types:</p>
  <ul>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>Private General Practitioners</p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>Private Nurses</p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>Private Pharmacists</p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>Private Optometrists</p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>Private Physiotherapists</p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>Private Radiographers</p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>Private Podiatrists.</p>
         </div>
      </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
Each Private Controlled Drug Prescriber is linked to one 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_sustainability_and_transformation_partnership">Sustainability and Transformation Partnership</xref>
 (
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_sustainability_and_transformation_partnership">STP</xref>
). This is the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_sustainability_and_transformation_partnership">Sustainability and Transformation Partnership</xref>
 that is responsible for the Private Controlled Drug Prescriber and may not necessarily be the geographic 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_sustainability_and_transformation_partnership">Sustainability and Transformation Partnership</xref>
.  </p>
